write a python function to read from an excel spreadsheet.
Sure, here's an example Python code for reading data from an Excel file using the openpyxl library:
```python
import openpyxl
def read_excel(file_path):
    wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(file_path)
    sheet = wb['Sheet1']
    for row in range(sheet.nrows):
        print('Row {}: {}'.format(row+1, sheet.cell(row=row, column=1).value))
```
This function takes the file path as an argument and loads the Excel workbook using openpyxl. It then selects the first sheet in the workbook and iterates over each row, printing out the value of the first cell in that row. You can modify this code to read data from other cells or sheets by changing the selection criteria accordingly.
